This paper is about parallelization of online learning, which is a core primitive in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between delay, degree of parallelism, representation power, and empirical performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper presents preliminary empirical results, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
